dard MFN, similar range."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does your team handle Ukrainian EDI for international brands?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We operate within your supplier portal as the operational partner. Vchasno (most popular general EDI) — invoice, delivery note, acceptance act generated in our WMS, signed with qualified electronic signature (QES) from our operator side. Comarch EDI for ATB (mandatory protocol). SAP Ariba for Metro. Edin for pharma. For international brands without Ukrainian QES — our QES suffices since the agency model places us as the legal seller to the Ukrainian chain. Your brand sees order-to-cash flow in real-time through our partner dashboard."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the cost of cross-border transportation US/EU/China to Ukraine?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"US→UA: $2,500-4,000 per 40ft container sea (30-45 days) or $8-12/kg air (15-21 days). UK→UA: $1,800-2,800 per 40ft container road+sea or $5-8/kg air (7-12 days). EU→UA (Germany, Poland, Netherlands): $1,200-2,000 per 40ft truck (5-10 days). China→UA: $2,000-3,500 per 40ft container sea (35-50 days via Black Sea/Odesa) or $6-10/kg air. This is a one-time cost per inventory replenishment, not per B2B order. For 50-pallet inbound — averages out to $30-80/pallet for transportation. Within Ukraine — delivery to retail chains is paid by the chain (FOB warehouse) and costs $30-60/pallet via Nova Poshta Cargo."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why has the Ukrainian B2B retail market opened up for international brands since 2022?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Russian and Belarusian suppliers exited the Ukrainian retail market following the 2022 invasion. Categories remain open across cosmetics (Watsons/Eva actively recruiting international beauty), premium food (Silpo expanding international portfolio), fashion (Modnakasta, INTERTOP, Kasta seeking international labels), household chemistry, textile, niche products. Retail chain