<!-- WHY UKRAINE OPENED UP -->
<section class="b2b-sec b2b-sec-light">
  <div class="ctr">
    <div class="b2b-chip b2b-chip-dark">MARKET OPPORTUNITY</div>
    <h2 class="b2b-h2">Why the Ukrainian B2B retail market opened for international brands in 2026</h2>
    <p class="b2b-lede">Russian and Belarusian suppliers exited the Ukrainian retail market following the 2022 invasion. Categories remain open across cosmetics, premium food, fashion, household chemistry, textile. Retail chains are actively reaching out to international suppliers with offers. Margin in Ukrainian retail is typically 30-50% above the brand's domestic market for premium categories.</p>
    <div class="b2b-uc-grid">
      <div class="b2b-uc-card">
        <div class="b2b-uc-num">36 MILLION</div>
        <h3>Fourth-largest Eastern European retail market</h3>
        <p>36 million people, median monthly income $580, growing middle class concentrated in Kyiv, Lviv, Odesa, Dnipro. Active retail infrastructure: 300+ Silpo premium food stores, 1,500+ ATB mass food, 800+ Watsons and Eva beauty chain locations, plus regional chains. Total annual B2B logistics flow $2-3 billion.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="b2b-uc-card">
        <div class="b2b-uc-num">2022 EXIT</div>
        <h3>Open category niches after RF/BY supplier exit</h3>
        <p>Cosmetics, premium food, fashion, household chemistry — categories where Ukrainian retail actively seeks international alternatives. Watsons and Eva have dedicated programs for international beauty brand entry. Silpo and Metro actively recruit European premium food. Modnakasta and INTERTOP openly source international fashion labels.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="b2b-uc-card">
        <div class="b2b-uc-num">30-50%</div>
        <h3>Margin uplift vs brand's domestic market</h3>
        <p>Premium beauty, premium food, fashion — Ukrainian retail prices typically 30-50% above brand's domestic equivalent. Watsons/Brocard premium beauty pricing comparable to Sephora EU. Silpo premium food pricing comparable to Waitrose mid-tier. Margin captured by international brand entering with cost-efficient Ukraine fulfillment vs running country direct.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="b2b-uc-card">
        <div class="b2b-uc-num">DCFTA</div>
        <h3>EU-Ukraine and UK-Ukraine free trade areas</h3>
        <p>EU brands benefit from EU-Ukraine DCFTA — zero or reduced import duties for most categories. UK brands benefit from UK-Ukraine FTA. US brands — standard MFN tariffs typically 0-10%. Customs clearance process well-established with multiple specialized brokers. Average customs clearance time 1-3 business days.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="b2b-uc-card">
        <div class="b2b-uc-num">AGENCY</div>
        <h3>Agency model — no Ukrainian legal entity required</h3>
        <p>Through our Ukrainian operational partner under agency agreement. Your brand remains a US LLC, UK Ltd, German GmbH, etc. We act as the Ukrainian legal counterparty to the retail chain. All Ukrainian compliance (VAT, accounting, EDI signature, alcohol/pharma licenses) on our side. You receive monthly settlement in USD/EUR to your home-country account.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="b2b-uc-card">
        <div class="b2b-uc-num">USD/EUR</div>
        <h3>Currency risk on us, not on you</h3>
        <p>Ukrainian hryvnia carries war-related currency risk. Our model: Ukrainian retail pays us in UAH, we convert at NBU daily rate and remit to you in USD or EUR to your bank account in the US, UK, Germany, Poland, or wherever. Conversion fee 0.5-1%. Settlement SLA 5 business days. Currency risk taken by us — you see only USD/EUR.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- HOW IT WORKS for international brand -->
<section class="b2b-sec">
  <div class="ctr">
    <div class="b2b-chip b2b-chip-dark">OPERATIONAL FLOW</div>
    <h2 class="b2b-h2">8 steps from contract to first shipment to Ukrainian retail chain</h2>
    <ol class="b2b-flow-steps">
      <li><strong>1. Contract with our Ukrainian operational partner (days 1-3).</strong> Agency agreement. Your international brand stays in its home jurisdiction. Our partner sells on your behalf to Ukrainian retail. Contract specifies SLA, rates, USD/EUR settlement terms, liability.</li>
      <li><strong>2. Documentation prep from your side (days 3-7).</strong> Corporate registration documents, banking info, commercial invoice for first inbound, certificate of origin (EUR.1 for EU, US-Ukraine for US, UK-Ukraine for UK), HS code classification. For alcohol — excise documentation. For food/pharma — quality certificates.</li>
      <li><strong>3. International transportation (days 7-14).</strong> US→UA: 30-45 days sea via Black Sea/Odesa or 15-21 days air. UK→UA: 7-12 days road+sea or 3-5 days air. EU→UA (DE/PL/NL): 5-10 days truck. China→UA: 35-50 days sea or 8-15 days air. Ukrainian import declaration at border, 20% VAT payment, customs clearance 1-3 business days.</li>
      <li><strong>4. Inbound and WMS slotting (days 14-16).</strong> Receive shipment, photo-document condition, verify against commercial invoice. Each SKU gets WMS slot tied to your brand. Alcohol — separate licensed zone at Bilohorodka facility. Food/cosmetics — FEFO zone. Premium goods — separate secure area.</li>
      <li><strong>5. Supplier registration with retail chain (days 16-21).</strong> Documentation package for Silpo, ATB, Watsons, Eva, Metro, Modnakasta, INTERTOP. Our operational partner already has supplier status with most major chains — your brand plugs in through us as a new supplier in our portfolio.</li>
      <li><strong>6. EDI protocol setup (days 21-25).</strong> Vchasno EDI for general documentation. Comarch EDI for ATB. SAP Ariba for Metro. Edin for pharma. Invoices, delivery notes, acceptance acts generated in our WMS, signed with qualified electronic signature from our operator side.</li>
      <li><strong>7. First test shipment end-to-end (days 25-30).</strong> Test order from the retail chain for 1-2 pallets to validate full cycle: pick → EDI documents → Nova Poshta Cargo → chain receiving → EDI check-in → status "delivered" → invoice to chain. If all works — go production.</li>
      <li><strong>8. Production + monthly USD/EUR settlement.</strong> Chain orders flow into our WMS, we pick-pack-document-ship. Monthly settlement: Ukrainian revenue minus fulfillment fee minus customs costs minus commission = net USD/EUR remitted to your bank account. Settlement SLA 5 business days. NBU daily conversion rate.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- INTERNATIONAL BRAND USE CASES -->
<section class="b2b-sec b2b-sec-light">
  <div class="ctr">
    <div class="b2b-chip b2b-chip-dark">USE CASES</div>
    <h2 class="b2b-h2">Six international brand scenarios we operate in 2026</h2>
    <div class="b2b-tech-grid">
      <div class="b2b-tech-card">
        <h3>🇺🇸 US beauty → Eva / Watsons</h3>
        <p>US natural beauty brand (clean ingredients, indie premium) entering Ukrainian beauty retail. Eva and Watsons actively recruit US niche labels. Volume per typical brand: 8-25 pallets/month. Cross-border US→UA via sea container 30-45 days (cost-efficient for non-perishable). Margin in Ukrainian retail typically 35-45% above US DTC pricing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="b2b-tech-card">
        <h3>🇬🇧 UK premium food → Silpo / Novus</h3>
        <p>UK premium food brand (gourmet, organic, niche) entering Ukrainian premium food retail. Silpo and Novus actively expanding international portfolios. Volume per typical brand: 5-15 pallets/month. Cross-border UK→UA via road+sea 7-12 days or air 3-5 days for perishables. UK-Ukraine FTA = zero import duties for most categories.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="b2b-tech-card">
        <h3>🇩🇪 German FMCG → ATB / Auchan</h3>
        <p>German FMCG brand (cleaning products, household chemistry, personal care) entering Ukrainian mass retail. ATB and Auchan actively recruit German FMCG to replace exited Russian/Belarusian suppliers. Volume per typical brand: 15-40 pallets/month. Cross-border DE→UA via truck 5-7 days. EU-Ukraine DCFTA = zero import duties for most categories.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="b2b-tech-card">
        <h3>🇮🇹 Italian fashion → Modnakasta / INTERTOP</h3>
        <p>Italian fashion brand (apparel, footwear, accessories — mid-premium tier) entering Ukrainian fashion retail. Modnakasta and INTERTOP openly source international labels. Volume per typical brand: 10-25 pallets/month seasonal. Cross-border IT→UA via truck 7-10 days. EU-Ukraine DCFTA = zero duties on most fashion categories.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="b2b-tech-card">
        <h3>🇵🇱 Polish beauty → Eva / Prostor / Cosmo</h3>
        <p>Polish beauty brand (Inglot, Bielenda, Eveline-style — mass-market premium) entering Ukrainian beauty retail. Eva, Prostor, Cosmo actively recruit Polish beauty given geographic proximity and supply chain stability. Volume per typical brand: 12-30 pallets/month. Cross-border PL→UA via truck 3-5 days. EU-Ukraine DCFTA.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="b2b-tech-card">
        <h3>🇫🇷🇪🇸 Premium wine → Wine.ua / Silpo wine</h3>
        <p>French and Spanish wine brands entering Ukrainian wine retail. Wine.ua, Silpo wine section, Novus wine, premium wine shops actively expanding international portfolios. Volume per typical brand: 3-12 pallets/month. Cross-border FR/ES→UA via truck 8-12 days. Alcohol licensed zone at our Bilohorodka facility. Excise documentation handled by our operator.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PRICING -->
<section class="b2b-sec" id="b2b-cta">
  <div class="ctr">
