    <h2 class="b2b-h2">Cost arbitrage + open market window — Ukrainian B2B fulfillment for international wholesale brands</h2>
    <p>The Ukrainian B2B retail market has opened up substantially since 2022 for international brands. Russian and Belarusian suppliers exited following the invasion, leaving categories open across cosmetics, premium food, fashion, household chemistry, textile, and niche segments. Retail chains (Silpo, ATB, Watsons, Eva, Metro, Modnakasta, INTERTOP) actively reach out to international suppliers — Watsons has a dedicated international beauty entry program, Silpo expanding premium food portfolios, Modnakasta openly sourcing international fashion labels.</p>
    <p>Cost arbitrage is the second compelling factor. Pallet storage in Ukraine costs $10/month vs $35-50 US 3PL vs $40-65 EU 3PL. B2B order pick & pack costs $0.41/order vs $1.20-1.80 US vs $1.80-2.50 EU. Annual cost for a typical international wholesale brand running 50 pallets and 200 B2B orders/month: $6,000-7,000 in Ukraine vs $24,000-30,000 in the US vs $30,000-40,000 in the EU. The 3-5x cost differential is driven by Ukrainian labor cost ($600-800/mo warehouse worker vs $3,000-4,500 US, $2,200-2,800 EU) and warehouse real estate cost ($35-50/sqm/year vs $120-180 US, $100-150 EU). Quality (99.98% pick accuracy, 24h SLA, full EDI integration) is comparable to US/EU 3PL because we run the same WMS technology stack.</p>
    <p>Our agency model eliminates the key barrier — no need to set up a Ukrainian legal entity. Your international brand remains a US LLC, UK Ltd, German GmbH, Italian SpA, French SAS, Polish Sp. z o.o., or whatever your home jurisdiction. Our Ukrainian operational partner acts as the legal counterparty to the Ukrainian retail chain under an agency agreement. All Ukrainian compliance (VAT registration, accounting, EDI qualified electronic signature, alcohol/pharma licenses where applicable) is on our side. You receive monthly revenue settlement in USD or EUR to your home-country bank account. Currency risk of the Ukrainian hryvnia is on us — Ukrainian retail pays us in UAH, we convert at NBU daily rate, you see only USD/EUR with a 0.5-1% conversion fee and 5-business-day settlement SLA.</p>
    <p>Onboarding timeline is 21-30 business days from contract signing to first shipment to a Ukrainian retail chain. Cycle: contract with our Ukrainian operational partner, documentation prep from your side, international transportation (US 15-45 days, EU 5-10 days, UK 7-12 days, China 35-50 days), inbound and WMS slotting, supplier registration with the retail chain through our partner, EDI protocol setup (Comarch for ATB, SAP Ariba for Metro, Vchasno for general), test shipment, then production. Our operational partner already has supplier status with 30+ major Ukrainian retail chains — saving 2-4 months versus traditional supplier registration where each brand registers with each chain from scratch.</p>
    <p>War risk is real but managed. Facilities are 35-45km from Kyiv center, outside primary missile impact zones. Mitigation: war-risk insurance ($0.30-0.80 per $100 of inventory value monthly), 30-day inventory cap practice, generator backup and blast protection, zero days of operational downtime across our customer base since February 2022, government compensation scheme for damaged commercial property. International brands typically include insurance as a standard line item and operate normally.</p>
